Fitzhugh has granted me permission to create a non-Doodle-related post in honor of our Leolicious.
Leo's back story is a bit convoluted, but here's the important part: when he got away from his new adoptive family, they washed their hands of him. He was in no way equipped to be an outdoor cat and was suddenly running loose, fending for himself. Over the next 7 months my mom & I made the 40-minute drive to the neighborhood he'd last been spotted in on an almost daily basis to try to find him. IT TOOK US SEVEN MONTHS TO FINALLY CATCH HIM. I cannot describe how frustrating, devastating and defeating it was to continue our rescue attempts, but we never gave up. We just couldn't.
On Jan. 27, 2014, Leo was FINALLY safely caught & brought to my parentsâ€™ house. We had never intended to add Leo to our motley crew, but after all that work -- how could we not?

Happy anniversary, Smoochie Woochie. I love you so much.

AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION!!! Meet Roxy, a Boxer/Bulldog mix puppy born around 11/30/2017. Roxy is a sweet, endearing little girl who will steal your heart as soon as you hold her. She came to the rescue from a local shelter where a good samaritan had found her and brought her there. She is such a sweetheart that the shelter assistant manager held her in her lap until our rescue arrived to get her! At home, Roxy has started her crate and house training. She has many foster brothers and sisters to play with, and loves every minute of it! Her favorite game is tug of war with any dog who will play with her. She loves to run and play in her fenced in backyard. But her most favorite thing is to cuddle and sleep in your arms. She is one of the best companions a person could ask for! And yes, she has that cute Bulldog snore when she sleeps. She currently weighs 12 pounds and may weigh 50 to 60 pounds when full grown. Roxy is current with her vaccines and her adoption fee will include her future spay, rabies, and microchip.
